# List All Available Tools

List all available tools including both built-in development tools and MCP integrations. Display in bullet format with brief descriptions and key parameters.

## Built-in Development Tools
- Read(file_path, offset?, limit?) - Read file contents with line numbers
- Write(file_path, content) - Write or overwrite files
- Edit(file_path, old_string, new_string, replace_all?) - Perform exact string replacements
- Glob(pattern, path?) - Fast file pattern matching with glob patterns
- Grep(pattern, path?, output_mode?, glob?, type?) - Search code with ripgrep
- Bash(command, timeout?, run_in_background?) - Execute bash commands
- NotebookEdit(notebook_path, new_source, cell_id?, edit_mode?) - Edit Jupyter notebook cells

## Task & Planning Tools
- Task(subagent_type, prompt, description) - Launch specialized agents (Bash, Explore, Plan, general-purpose)
- TodoWrite(todos) - Create and manage task lists
- EnterPlanMode() - Enter planning mode for implementation tasks
- ExitPlanMode(allowedPrompts?, launchSwarm?) - Exit planning mode and request approval
- AskUserQuestion(questions) - Ask user questions with multiple choice options
- Skill(skill, args?) - Execute slash commands programmatically

## MCP Tools

### GitHub Integration
- search_code(query, page?, perPage?) - Fast code search across all GitHub repositories
- search_repositories(query, sort?, order?) - Find repositories by name, description, topics
- search_issues(query, sort?, order?) - Search issues using GitHub syntax
- search_pull_requests(query, sort?, order?) - Search pull requests
- create_pull_request(owner, repo, title, head, base, body?) - Create new pull request
- update_pull_request(owner, repo, pullNumber, title?, body?, state?) - Update existing PR
- merge_pull_request(owner, repo, pullNumber, merge_method?) - Merge pull request
- list_issues(owner, repo, state?, labels?, perPage?) - List repository issues
- issue_read(method, owner, repo, issue_number) - Get issue details/comments/labels
- issue_write(method, owner, repo, title?, body?, labels?) - Create or update issues
- add_issue_comment(owner, repo, issue_number, body) - Comment on issues
- pull_request_read(method, owner, repo, pullNumber) - Get PR details/diff/status/files/reviews
- create_or_update_file(owner, repo, path, content, message, branch, sha?) - Create/update single file
- push_files(owner, repo, branch, files, message) - Push multiple files in one commit
- get_file_contents(owner, repo, path?, ref?) - Get file/directory contents
- create_branch(owner, repo, branch, from_branch?) - Create new branch
- list_branches(owner, repo, page?, perPage?) - List repository branches
- list_commits(owner, repo, sha?, author?, perPage?) - Get commit list
- get_commit(owner, repo, sha, include_diff?) - Get commit details

### Browser Automation (Playwright)
- browser_navigate(url) - Navigate to URL
- browser_snapshot() - Capture accessibility snapshot (better than screenshot)
- browser_take_screenshot(filename?, fullPage?, type?) - Take screenshot
- browser_click(ref, element, button?, doubleClick?) - Click elements
- browser_type(ref, element, text, slowly?, submit?) - Type text into elements
- browser_fill_form(fields) - Fill multiple form fields
- browser_evaluate(function, ref?, element?) - Execute JavaScript
- browser_wait_for(text?, textGone?, time?) - Wait for conditions
- browser_close() - Close browser page

### Web Scraping (Firecrawl)
- firecrawl_scrape(url, formats?, onlyMainContent?) - Scrape single URL (fastest, most reliable)
- firecrawl_search(query, limit?, sources?, scrapeOptions?) - Search web and extract content
- firecrawl_map(url, limit?, search?) - Discover URLs on a website
- firecrawl_crawl(url, limit?, maxDiscoveryDepth?, scrapeOptions?) - Crawl website pages
- firecrawl_extract(urls, prompt?, schema?) - Extract structured data with LLM

### Context7 Library Documentation
- resolve-library-id(libraryName) - Resolve package name to Context7-compatible library ID
- get-library-docs(context7CompatibleLibraryID, topic?, tokens?) - Fetch up-to-date library documentation

### Git Operations (Local)
- git_status(repo_path) - Show working tree status
- git_diff(repo_path, target) - Show differences between branches/commits
- git_diff_staged(repo_path) - Show staged changes
- git_diff_unstaged(repo_path) - Show unstaged changes
- git_log(repo_path, max_count?) - Show commit logs
- git_add(repo_path, files) - Add files to staging
- git_commit(repo_path, message) - Record changes
- git_create_branch(repo_path, branch_name, base_branch?) - Create new branch
- git_checkout(repo_path, branch_name) - Switch branches

## Specialized Tools
- WebFetch(url, prompt) - Fetch and analyze web content with AI
- WebSearch(query, allowed_domains?, blocked_domains?) - Search web with DuckDuckGo
- KillShell(shell_id) - Kill running background bash shell
- TaskOutput(task_id, block?, timeout?) - Get output from background task

## MCP Server Management
- mcp-find(query, limit?) - Find MCP servers in catalog
- mcp-add(name, activate?) - Add MCP server to session
- mcp-config-set(server, config) - Configure MCP server
- mcp-remove(name) - Remove MCP server
- mcp-exec(name, arguments?) - Execute tool from any MCP server

## MCP Resources
- ListMcpResourcesTool(server?) - List available resources from MCP servers
- ReadMcpResourceTool(server, uri) - Read specific resource from MCP server
